The paper deals with the problem of estimating degree distribution moments of an undirected graph in sublinear time, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms and has applications in various fields. The paper proposes a new algorithm that is significantly simpler than previous algorithms and has a query complexity connected to the arboricity of the graph. Therefore, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), as these sub-categories are relevant to the problem and the proposed algorithm.
